---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import screenshot1 from '../assets/1.png';
import screenshot2 from '../assets/2.png';

const title = 'fun clicker';
const description =
  'The ultimate guide to Fun Clicker. Explore the twisted lore of the Scratch Clicker sensation, master the shop strategy, and survive the realistic transformation.';

const gameUrl = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_GAME_URL ?? 'https://webresources.cc/clicker/fun-clicker.html';
---

<SiteLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/">
  <section id="game" class="text-center space-y-10">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h1 class="hero-text text-5xl md:text-7xl font-black uppercase italic">
        SCRATCH<br />CLICKER.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-gray-400">Atmospheric Horror Behind the Smile</p>
    </div>

    <div id="game-shell" class="bg-black neo-border shadow-brutal aspect-video overflow-hidden group">
      <iframe
        id="game-frame"
        src={gameUrl}
        data-base-src={gameUrl}
        class="w-full h-full"
        title="Fun Clicker Game Window"
        loading="lazy"
        allowfullscreen
        allow="fullscreen"
        referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"
      ></iframe>
    </div>

    <div class="flex justify-center gap-4 text-[10px] font-black uppercase">
      <span class="bg-neo-yellow neo-border px-3 py-1 shadow-brutal-sm">Viral on YouTube</span>
      <span class="bg-neo-blue neo-border px-3 py-1 shadow-brutal-sm">v1.4 Updated</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400">
      fun clicker guide, fun clicker tips, fun clicker FAQ.
    </p>

    <div class="flex justify-center gap-3 pt-2 text-[10px] font-black uppercase">
      <button
        id="btn-fullscreen"
        type="button"
        class="bg-white neo-border px-4 py-2 hover:translate-x-1 hover:translate-y-1 transition-all shadow-brutal-sm"
      >
        FULLSCREEN
      </button>
      <button
        id="btn-reload"
        type="button"
        class="bg-black text-white neo-border px-4 py-2 hover:translate-x-1 hover:translate-y-1 transition-all shadow-brutal-sm"
      >
        RELOAD
      </button>
    </div>

    <script is:inline>
      (() => {
        const frame = document.getElementById('game-frame');
        const shell = document.getElementById('game-shell');
        const btnReload = document.getElementById('btn-reload');
        const btnFullscreen = document.getElementById('btn-fullscreen');

        if (btnReload && frame) {
          btnReload.addEventListener('click', () => {
            const base = frame.getAttribute('data-base-src') || frame.getAttribute('src') || '';
            if (!base) return;
            const url = new URL(base, window.location.href);
            url.searchParams.set('r', String(Date.now()));
            frame.setAttribute('src', url.toString());
          });
        }

        if (btnFullscreen && shell) {
          btnFullscreen.addEventListener('click', async () => {
            try {
              if (!document.fullscreenElement) {
                await shell.requestFullscreen();
              } else {
                await document.exitFullscreen();
              }
            } catch {
              // No-op if fullscreen is blocked by browser policies.
            }
          });
        }
      })();
    </script>
  </section>

  <section id="screenshots" class="space-y-10 bg-gray-50 -mx-6 px-6 py-16">
    <div class="space-y-3 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black uppercase italic">Screenshots</h2>
      <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-gray-400">fun clicker gameplay moments</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <figure class="bg-white neo-border shadow-brutal-sm overflow-hidden">
        <Image
          src={screenshot1}
          alt="fun clicker screenshot showing the game interface"
          class="w-full h-auto"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          widths={[622, 1244]}
          sizes="(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 100vw"
        />
        <figcaption class="p-4 border-t border-black text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-600">
          fun clicker screenshot 01
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure class="bg-white neo-border shadow-brutal-sm overflow-hidden">
        <Image
          src={screenshot2}
          alt="fun clicker screenshot with upgraded progression"
          class="w-full h-auto"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          widths={[633, 1266]}
          sizes="(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 100vw"
        />
        <figcaption class="p-4 border-t border-black text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-600">
          fun clicker screenshot 02
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="about" class="space-y-8">
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-12">
      <div class="md:w-1/3">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase leading-none sticky top-24">ABOUT<br />FUN<br />CLICKER.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="md:w-2/3 space-y-6 text-sm font-medium leading-loose text-gray-700">
        <p class="first-letter:text-4xl first-letter:font-black first-letter:mr-2 first-letter:float-left">
          In the vast landscape of online browser games, few titles manage to subvert expectations quite like
          <strong> Fun Clicker</strong>. At first glance, it appears to be a rudimentary, cheerful idle game. However,
          as players delve deeper, they quickly realize it is a masterclass in gradual atmospheric horror, hiding a
          dark narrative behind its colorful facade.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-neo-yellow neo-border p-6 shadow-brutal-sm text-black">
          <h3 class="font-black uppercase mb-2">The &quot;Human&quot; Experiment</h3>
          <p class="italic">
            &quot;I want to be human again...&quot; Quotes like these suggest the entity isn&apos;t just a graphic; it&apos;s a
            trapped soul in a digital prison. As you click, the entity attempts to metamorphose, but the process is
            flawed, leading to the emergence of the &quot;Spider&quot; form.
          </p>
        </div>
        <p>
          This game serves as a metaphor for how the pursuit of high scores can strip away humanity, leaving only a
          monstrosity behind. It&apos;s an environmental narrative that shifts from innocent joy to a void-like tragedy.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="mechanics" class="space-y-12 bg-gray-50 -mx-6 px-6 py-16">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-black uppercase italic text-center">Gameplay Mechanics</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase bg-black text-white inline-block px-2">The Shop Guide</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-black pl-4">
            <p class="font-black text-xs">+1 CLICK (COST: 25)</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">The starter essential to get the ball rolling.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 border-black pl-4">
            <p class="font-black text-xs">+20 CLICK (COST: 250)</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">The first major power spike. Visual pacing accelerates here.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 border-black pl-4">
            <p class="font-black text-xs">+100 CLICK (COST: 1K)</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">The mid-game standard. Spam this to reach millions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 border-black pl-4">
            <p class="font-black text-xs">+1 SLAVE / +30 SLAVE</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              Increases CPS automatically. Noted by many players as a strange but effective upgrade.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neo-blue neo-border p-6 shadow-brutal space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase">Mystery Click Wheel</h3>
        <p class="text-xs font-bold leading-relaxed">
          Occasionally, a blue face appears. Clicking this spins a wheel of destiny.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-black"></span> Rewards: Massive click bonuses</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-black"></span> Punishments: Land on Negative Time</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="w-2 h-2 bg-black"></span> Strategy: Ignore early game, use in late game</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="characters" class="space-y-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase border-b-4 border-black pb-2">Faces of Degradation</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-12">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6">
        <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-neo-green neo-border flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-3xl shadow-brutal-sm">
          üôÇ
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h3 class="font-black uppercase">1. The Green Smiley (The Innocent)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed font-medium">
            The default state. Resembles early internet emojis. Represents the &quot;Facade&quot; before your aggressive
            clicking begins to corrupt the entity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 border-t border-dashed border-black pt-8">
        <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-white neo-border flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-3xl shadow-brutal-sm overflow-hidden">
          <span class="grayscale contrast-125">üëÅÔ∏è</span>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h3 class="font-black uppercase text-red-600">4. The Realistic Abomination</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed font-medium">
            The cartoon style vanishes. The face gains hyper-realistic human eyes and lips. It creates a sense of
            revulsion, bridging the gap between idle game and body horror.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 border-t border-dashed border-black pt-8">
        <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-black text-white neo-border flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-3xl shadow-brutal-sm">
          üï∑Ô∏è
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h3 class="font-black uppercase italic">5. The Spider / Void (The End)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed font-medium font-bold italic underline">
            Sprouts realistic spider legs or becomes a black void. Heavily inspired by entities like &quot;Seek&quot; from
            Roblox Doors. It is a jumpscare waiting to happen.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 border-none">
    <div class="bg-black text-white p-8 neo-border shadow-brutal space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase italic text-neo-yellow">Pro Strategies</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-xs font-bold tracking-wide">
        <div>
          <p class="text-neo-blue">01. Butterfly Click Method</p>
          <p class="opacity-70">Use two fingers to alternate rapidly on the mouse button to bypass the early game grind.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-neo-blue">02. Prioritize Percentage</p>
          <p class="opacity-70">Always calculate value. The &quot;+1 Click&quot; becomes useless fast; save for the &quot;+100 Click&quot; early on.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-neo-blue">03. Watch the Eyes</p>
          <p class="opacity-70">The eyes track your cursor. If they stop and stare forward, a jumpscare or dialogue is imminent.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-8 neo-border shadow-brutal space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase">Viral Trends</h2>
      <p class="text-xs font-medium leading-loose text-gray-600">
        Creators like <strong>PghLFilms</strong> propelled Fun Clicker into the spotlight. Viewers love the shock
        factor, the sudden transition from a happy green circle to a realistic spider monster is perfect for short-form
        content.
      </p>
      <div class="pt-4 border-t-2 border-black flex items-center justify-between text-[10px] font-black uppercase">
        <span>YouTube Favorite</span>
        <span>#HorrorGames</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="faq" class="space-y-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase italic bg-neo-pink inline-block px-2">Essential FAQ</h2>
    <div class="divide-y-2 divide-black">
      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          How do I save my progress in fun clicker?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          fun clicker uses local browser storage. As long as you don&apos;t clear site data, your clicks and upgrades will
          still be there.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          What does &quot;Ultra Fun Mode&quot; do in fun clicker?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          It&apos;s the ultimate bait. Many players report a palette swap or a &quot;fake&quot; restart, reinforcing the game&apos;s
          no-escape theme.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          How do I unblock fun clicker at school or work?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          Some networks block game sites by category. If fun clicker is blocked, you&apos;ll need to use an approved
          network or ask your admin for access.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          Why is there a &quot;Slaves&quot; upgrade name in fun clicker?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          It&apos;s a controversial label used in some Scratch clicker clones. In practice it functions as an auto-clicker
          style CPS booster.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          What is fun clicker, exactly?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          fun clicker looks like a simple idle clicker, but it&apos;s structured like an atmospheric horror vignette: the
          visuals degrade as your numbers climb.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          Is fun clicker safe to play in a browser?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          fun clicker runs in the browser. As with any embed, keep your browser updated and avoid entering personal
          information into popups or unknown pages.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          Does fun clicker work on mobile?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          Usually yes, but some clicker builds behave differently on iOS/Android browsers. If taps don&apos;t register,
          try another browser or reload.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          What is CPS and why does it matter in fun clicker?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          CPS means clicks per second. In fun clicker, CPS upgrades push you through transformations without constant
          manual clicking.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          What are the best early upgrades for fun clicker?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          Start with small click boosts to break out of the slow opening, then aim for the bigger multipliers like
          +20 and +100 when they become affordable.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          Why do the eyes follow the cursor in fun clicker?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          It&apos;s a simple interaction trick that makes the &quot;face&quot; feel present. When the tracking breaks or locks,
          it can signal a scripted moment.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          How many skins or stages does fun clicker have?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          fun clicker is known for a cheerful start that escalates into realistic eyes and, eventually, spider or void
          imagery. The exact path can vary by build.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          What triggers the scary transformations in fun clicker?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          Usually it&apos;s tied to your total clicks, specific purchases, or timed events. The slow ramp is part of what
          makes fun clicker unsettling.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          How do I reset fun clicker progress?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          Clearing site data for this origin (cookies/local storage) typically resets the save. You can also try a
          private window to start fresh.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          How do I play fun clicker in fullscreen on this site?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          Use the FULLSCREEN button under the game. If your browser blocks it, click inside the game frame and try
          again.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          The game froze. How do I reload fun clicker fast?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          Use the RELOAD button under the frame. It forces the embedded page to refresh (even across domains) without
          reloading the whole site.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          Does fun clicker have an ending?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          Most versions are designed as a loop: you chase bigger numbers while the world gets darker. Some builds add a
          final void/spider state as a soft endpoint.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="py-6 group cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="font-black text-lg uppercase flex justify-between items-center list-none">
          Why does fun clicker feel like horror even though it&apos;s a clicker?
          <span class="group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 italic">
          It weaponizes repetition. The same action that makes numbers go up also erodes the mascot, turning progress
          into a kind of body-horror story.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
